Repost @oniceperspectives

After watching @the.skate.kid’s performance to Andra Day’s uplifting anthem on Black Lives Matter Plaza last June, and seeing her perform again on TV at yesterday’s inauguration, it became clear to me just how much the art of skating can and always has affected our national identity.
❄️
We filmed this on Christmas Day 2018 (hence the crowd!). MK has devoted her entire post-Olympic career to public service, first the U.S. Department of State, and then to the Clinton and Biden campaigns, as a public envoy for diplomacy and outreach. And it won’t stop there.
❄️
Thank you Kaitlyn Saunders (@the.skate.kid), Michelle Kwan, Andra Day and the millions of hearts and artists out there who made yesterday possible. Let’s keep rising up, and fighting for a better, more diverse, tolerant, and inclusive future, for our sport and our world. __⛸
❄️
__🎥 Jordan @oniceperspectives
__⛸ @michellewkwan
__👣 Choreo @karenwkwan
__🎵 Rise Up @andraday
__📍 @iceatsantamonica @dtsantamonica 
__🗓 December 25, 2018

node.text:
A very fast skater meal done in less than 10 mins. I made pesto shrimp and zoodles for lunch. It’s so easy and what I found in my kitchen. I didn’t bother making the pesto sauce but found a jar hiding in the pantry😉

Two large zucchini spiralized 
2-3 tbsp Parmesan cheese 
1 tbsp olive oil
2 cloves of garlic
Pepper to taste 
Shrimp in pesto (if you have time you should make your own pesto🤩) Put olive oil in pan, throw chopped garlic and cook for 30 seconds to a minute. Add zoodles and use tongs to turn it from time to time. Don’t overcook, you want the zoodles to be al dente. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and place cooked pesto shrimp on top. #skatermeals

node.text: Thrilled to announce the premiere of the @youtube original show “Recipe for Change” which I co-executive produced with @thespringhillco team. I’m joined by powerful voices as we gather around the dinner table to celebrate Asian Pacific Islander culture and ignite change. Set a reminder to watch on June 30th, only on @YouTube: yt.be/recipeforchange (link in bio too!).

node.text: Happy #OlympicDay! No higher honor than to represent the United States and compete in the Olympic Games. The Olympic creed is what I believed in as an athlete and it rings true for all of life: "The important thing in life is not the triumph, but the fight; the essential thing is not to have won, but to have fought well."
